HEADWORD: Mobility
<hw>Mo*bil"i*ty</hw> <pr>(m⟦osl⟧*b⟦icr⟧l"⟦icr⟧*t⟦ycr⟧)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>mobilitas</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>mobilit⟦eacute⟧</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The quality or state
of being mobile; <as>as, the <ex>mobility</ex> of a liquid, of an army,
of the populace, of features, of a muscle</as>.</def> <rj><au>Sir T.
Browne.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The mob; the lower classes.</def>
<mark>[Humorous]</mark> <rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mobilization</ent>⟦br⟧
